It absolutely needs to be noted that in Server 2019, the "Configure the Registration Authority" section calls to run the following powershell command:
`Set-AdfsCertificateAuthority -EnrollmentAgent -EnrollmentAgentCertificateTemplate WHFBEnrollmentAgent -WindowsHelloCertificateTemplate WHFBAuthentication`
Which WILL fail with the following error in a 100% on-prem configuration:
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/2928845/152263038-8553956b-11e4-406b-8d20-c2fcbb649fe6.png)
The ONLY workaround is to change the ADFS Authentication Methods to use 'Certificate Authentication' in the 'Primary' AND 'Additional' tab BEFORE running the aforementioned powershell command:
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/2928845/152263148-419ab142-2038-442e-8443-96f6aab3876e.png)
`Get-AdfsCertificateAuthority` can then be used to verify the options have been set appropriately:
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/2928845/152263273-20cdc577-6dd0-4931-a17e-25c0f4309f03.png)



